# Table Seating Planner

## Summary

The `TableSeatingPlanner` card is a comprehensive tool for managing event seating arrangements. It allows users to plan and organize seating for guests, tables, and other fixtures in a venue. The card provides features for importing guest lists, defining table layouts, and generating personalized invitations and seating information.

## Import

```javascript
import { TableSeatingPlanner } from '../table-seating-planner';
```

## Usage as a Field

The `TableSeatingPlanner` card can be used as a field within a consuming card or field. This allows you to embed the seating planner functionality directly into your application.

```javascript
import {
  CardDef,
  field,
  contains,
  linksToMany,
} from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';

export class EventCard extends CardDef {
  @field seatingPlanner = contains(TableSeatingPlanner);
  @field guests = linksToMany(() => Guest);
}
```

In this example, the `EventCard` contains a `seatingPlanner` field of type `TableSeatingPlanner`, allowing the event organizer to manage the seating arrangements directly within the event card.

## Template Usage

To use the `TableSeatingPlanner` card within a template, you can access its fields and components:

```handlebars
<BoxelCard>
  <@title>{{this.seatingPlanner.eventTitle}}</@title>
  <@body>
    <TableSeatingPlannerFitted @model={{this.seatingPlanner}} />
  </@body>
</BoxelCard>
```

In this example, the `TableSeatingPlannerFitted` component is used to render the seating planner within the event card's body. The `@model` parameter is bound to the `seatingPlanner` field of the current card.
